    <entry>
      <title>MATLAB-02结构化程式和自定义函数</title>
      <link href="/2023/10/09/MATLAB-02%E7%BB%93%E6%9E%84%E5%8C%96%E7%A8%8B%E5%BC%8F%E5%92%8C%E8%87%AA%E5%AE%9A%E4%B9%89%E5%87%BD%E6%95%B0/"/>
      <url>/2023/10/09/MATLAB-02%E7%BB%93%E6%9E%84%E5%8C%96%E7%A8%8B%E5%BC%8F%E5%92%8C%E8%87%AA%E5%AE%9A%E4%B9%89%E5%87%BD%E6%95%B0/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2 id="matlab-script">MATLAB Script</h2><ul><li>A file containing a series of MATLAB commands</li><li>Pretty much like a C/C++ program<ul><li>However Script does not need to be compiled before run</li></ul></li><li>Scripts need to be saved to as <code>&lt;file&gt;.m</code> filebefore they can be run</li></ul><p><code>%%</code> is the symbol of section, we can run a singlesection</p><p>use start indent to make code more readable</p><h3 id="script-flow">Script Flow</h3><ul><li>Typically scripts run from the first line to the last</li><li>Structured programming techniques(subroutine, loop. condition, etc.)are applied to make the program looks neat</li></ul><h3 id="flow-control">Flow Control</h3><p>[[MATLAB2~flow control.png]]</p><h3 id="rational-operators">Rational Operators</h3><p>[[MATLAB2~relational operator.png]]</p><h3 id="if-elseif-else">if elseif else</h3><figure class="highlight matlab"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">if</span> condition1</span><br><span class="line">statement1</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">elseif</span> condition2</span><br><span class="line">statement2</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">else</span></span><br><span class="line">statement3</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">end</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="switch">switch</h3><figure class="highlight matlab"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">switch</span> expression</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">case</span> value1</span><br><span class="line">statement1</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">case</span> value2</span><br><span class="line">statement2</span><br><span class="line">.</span><br><span class="line">.</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">otherwise</span></span><br><span class="line">statement</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">end</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="while">while</h3><figure class="highlight matlab"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">while</span> expression</span><br><span class="line">statement</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">end</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="for">for</h3><figure class="highlight matlab"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">for</span> varible = start: increment: <span class="keyword">end</span></span><br><span class="line">commands</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">end</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="pre-allocating-space-to-varibles">Pre-allocating Space toVaribles</h3><p>Method A:</p><figure class="highlight matlab"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">tic </span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">for</span> ii = <span class="number">1</span>:<span class="number">2000</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">for</span> jj = <span class="number">1</span>:<span class="number">2000</span></span><br><span class="line">        A(ii,jj) = ii + jj;</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">end</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">end</span></span><br><span class="line">toc</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">%历时 1.727258 秒。</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Method B:</p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">tic</span><br><span class="line">B = zeros(2000, 2000);</span><br><span class="line">for iii = 1:size(B,1)</span><br><span class="line">    for jjj = 1:size(B,2)</span><br><span class="line">        B(iii, jjj) = iii + jjj;</span><br><span class="line">    end</span><br><span class="line">end</span><br><span class="line">toc</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">%历时 0.020441 秒。</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Method B is faster, because method B used Pre-allocating.</p><p>The explanation of MATLAB:</p><blockquote><p>The size of the indicated variable or array appears to be changingwith each loop iteration.Commonly, this message appears because an arrayis growing by assignment or concatenation.Growing an array by assignmentor concatenation can be expensive.For large arrays,MATLAB must allocatea new block of memory and copy the older array contents to the new arrayas it makes each assignment.</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>Programs that change the size of a variable in this way can spendmost of their run time in this inefficient activity.There is alsosignificant overhead in shrinking an array on each iteration or inchanging the size of a variable on each iteration. In such cases,MATLABmust reallocate and copy the contents repeatedly.</p></blockquote><h3 id="break">break</h3><p>Used in iteration where convergence is not guaranteed.</p><h3 id="tips-for-script-writing">Tips for Script Writing</h3><ul><li>At the beginning of your script, use command<ul><li><code>clear all</code> to remove previous variables</li><li><code>close all</code> to close all figures</li></ul></li><li>Use semicolon <code>;</code> at the end of commands to inhibitunwanted output</li><li>Use ellipsis <code>...</code> to make scripts more readable<ul><li>MATLAB2020 and later version can break line with no need to useellipsis</li></ul></li><li>Press <code>Ctrl+C</code> to terminate the script before</li><li>conclusion</li></ul><h3 id="content-of-matlab-built-in-function">Content of MATLAB Built-inFunction</h3><figure class="highlight matlab"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">&gt;&gt;edit(which(<span class="string">&#x27;mean.m&#x27;</span>))</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">% open mean.m</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="function"><span class="keyword">function</span> <span class="title">y</span> = <span class="title">mean</span><span class="params">(x)</span></span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>In this example, function is a keyword, y is the name of outputvariable, mean is the name of function</p><h3 id="use-define-functions">Use Define Functions</h3><figure class="highlight matlab"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="function"><span class="keyword">function</span> <span class="title">x</span> = <span class="title">freebody</span><span class="params">(x0,v0,t)</span></span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">% calculation of free falling</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">% x0: initial displacement of in m</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">% v0: initial velocity in m/sec</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">% t: the elapsed time in sec</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">% x: the depth of falling in m</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">x = x0 + v0.*t + <span class="number">1</span>/<span class="number">2</span>*<span class="number">9.8</span>*t.*t;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Use the operator <code>.*</code> to support input vector.</p><p>For example, <code>freebody([0 1], [0 1], [10 20])</code> will output<code>[490 1981]</code></p><h3 id="function-with-multiple-inputs-and-outputs">Function withMultiple Inputs and Outputs</h3><ul><li>The acceleration of a particle and the force acting on it are asfollows:</li></ul><p><span class="math display">\[\begin{aligned}a &amp;= \frac{v_2 - v_1}{t_2 - t_1}\\F &amp;= ma\end{aligned}\]</span> <figure class="highlight matlab"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="function"><span class="keyword">function</span> <span class="params">[a F]</span> = <span class="title">acc</span><span class="params">(v2, v1, t2, t1, m)</span></span></span><br><span class="line">a = (v2 - v1)./(t2 - t1);</span><br><span class="line">F = m.*a;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><blockquote><p>[!note] output single variable as array X = acc(10, 5, 2, 1, 10); %X= 5 [X Y] = acc(10, 5, 2, 1, 10); %X = 5, Y = 50</p></blockquote><p>If we use the following form, the output will be a array.</p><figure class="highlight matlab"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="function"><span class="keyword">function</span> <span class="title">out</span> = <span class="title">acc</span><span class="params">(v2, v1, t2, t1, m)</span></span></span><br><span class="line">out(<span class="number">1</span>) = (v2 - v1)./(t2 - t1);</span><br><span class="line">out(<span class="number">2</span>) = m.*a;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">function converter</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">F = input(&#x27;The temperature in F: &#x27;);</span><br><span class="line">while ~isempty(F)</span><br><span class="line">    disp([&#x27;The temperature in C: &#x27; num2str((F-32)*5/9)]);</span><br><span class="line">    F = input(&#x27;The temperature in F: &#x27;);</span><br><span class="line">end</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="the-use-of-disp">The use of disp</h3><p><code>disp()</code> 仅接受一个参数，下面的这种写法是错误的：</p><p><code>disp('aaa',32)</code></p><p><code>disp(['aaa',78])</code>会输出'aaaN'，因为disp将78当做一个ASCII码字符作为显示</p><p>若想实现字符串和数字的混合输出，可以使用如下形式</p><p><code>disp(['aaa',num2str(32)])</code>，输出aaa32。</p><p><code>num2str()</code>函数将数字转换为字符类型数组，再通过矩阵的拼接，将两个字符类型数组拼接位一个数组，从而正常显示输出</p><blockquote><p>[!warning] 以下表达也可显示，但是显示形式不便于阅读</p></blockquote><blockquote><p><code>disp(&#123;'aaa',32&#125;)</code>：使用元胞数组，显示的内容为<code>&#123;'aaa'&#125;    &#123;[32]&#125;</code></p></blockquote><h3 id="function-default-variables">Function Default Variables</h3><p>函数参数意义</p><p>imputname 输入变量名列表</p><p>mfilename 函数源代码文件名</p><p>nargin 输入变量数</p><p>nargout 输出变量个数</p><p>varargin 可变长输入参数列表</p><p>varargout 可变长输出参数列表</p><table><thead><tr class="header"><th style="text-align: left;">Variables</th><th style="text-align: left;">Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="odd"><td style="text-align: left;">inputname</td><td style="text-align: left;">Variable name of function input</td></tr><tr class="even"><td style="text-align: left;">mfilename</td><td style="text-align: left;">File name of currently runningfunction</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td style="text-align: left;">nargin</td><td style="text-align: left;">Number of function input arguments</td></tr><tr class="even"><td style="text-align: left;">varargin</td><td style="text-align: left;">Variable length of argrument list</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td style="text-align: left;">varargout</td><td style="text-align: left;">Varible length output argument list</td></tr></tbody></table><h3 id="function-handle">Function Handle</h3><p>A way to create anonymous functions, i.e., one line expressionfunctions that do not have not have to be defined in .m files</p><figure class="highlight matlab"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">f = @(x) <span class="built_in">exp</span>(<span class="number">-2</span>*x);</span><br><span class="line">x = <span class="number">0</span>:<span class="number">0.1</span>:<span class="number">0.2</span>;</span><br><span class="line"><span class="built_in">plot</span>(x, f(x));</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>]]></content>
      
      
      
